TextView.android:text:
This is a software based on Android and used to control slam data acquisition devices. It communicates with the device via WiFi. The following is how to use the software:

 1) First, open WiFi and connect to the hotspot of the specified device;

 2) Click the 'CONNECT' button to connect to the server running on the device. After the connection is successful, you can see the prompt of successful connection in the 'Connection State' TextView;

 3) Click the 'START' button to start data collection;

 4) To end the acquisition, click the 'STOP' button, and the device will stop the acquisition and record the data into the internal storage of the device.

Of course, you can find this project in the link:

'https://github.com/Unsigned-Long/collector-controller'

Optimize the real-time performance of picture transmission. At present, pictures can be displayed in real time, but this is based on:

 1) Send pictures every few frames;

 2) What is transmitted is the picture after downsampling.
